<div class="hidden-content control-hide">
<p>② Respond to one of the following prompts:（三选一）</p>
<p>2A) Reflect on your membership in a community.Why is your involvement important to you?How has it shaped you?You may define community however you like.</p>
<p>2B) Yale students,faculty,and alumni engage issues of local,national,and international significance.Discuss an issue that is important to you and how your college experience could help you address it.</p>
<p>2C) Tell us about your relationship with a role model or mentor who has been influential in your life.How has their guidance been instrumental to your growth?</p>
<p><strong>Engineering Essay</strong></p>
<p>申请工程专业的还需完成一篇不超过250个单词的文书：</p>
<p>Please tell us more about what has led you to an interest in this field of study,what experiences(if any)you have had in engineering,and what it is about Yale’s engineering program that appeals to you.</p>
<p>对比了一下去年耶鲁的补充文书要求发现，短问题回答部分今年基本没变，只是第一个问题的字数限制从100个单词变成了125个单词。</p>
<p>短问题回答在耶鲁大学的申请中占主导地位，共有6个短问题需做回答，字数限制分别为不超过125个单词和35个单词。如此短的篇幅，你没有时间胡扯。没有空间让你用宽泛的陈述来圈出你的中心思想，必须直截了当地说到重点。</p>
<p>成功的申请人会选择一些精确的词汇，这些词汇能起到双重甚至三重作用——讲述你的故事(字面意思)、带来生动的细节以及突出你的整体智商。写一个好的短问题回答需要花费大量的文字功夫，所以要准备好花大量的时间来加工、修剪甚至推倒重来。</p>
<p>Essay部分，第一篇其实和去年差不多，是谈让你感兴趣的话题或想法，以及为何感兴趣，只是增加了和耶鲁课程挂钩的环节。</p>
<p>第二篇去年是二选一，今年增加了一个选择变成三选一。增加的话题是：告诉我们你和一个对你的生活有影响的榜样或导师的关系，他的指导对你的成长有什么帮助?</p>
<h1><strong>哥伦比亚大学</strong></h1>
<p>▷For the four list questions that follow,we ask that you list each individual response using commas or semicolons;the items do not have to be numbered or in any specific order.No explanatory text or formatting is needed.Please respond to each of the three short answer questions in 200 words or fewer.</p>
<p>▷List the titles of the required readings from academic courses that you enjoyed most during secondary/high school.</p>
<p>▷List the titles of the books,essays,poetry,short stories or plays you read outside of academic courses that you enjoyed most during secondary/high school.</p>
<p>▷List the titles of the print or digital publications,websites,journals,podcasts or other content with which you regularly engage.</p>
<p>▷List the movies,albums,shows,museums,lectures,events at your school or other entertainments that you enjoyed most during secondary/high school(in person or online).</p>
<p>▷Columbia students take an active role in improving their community,whether in their residence hall,classes or throughout New York City.Their actions,small or large,work to positively impact the lives of others.Share one contribution that you have made to your family,school,friend group or another community that surrounds you.(200 words or fewer)</p>
<p>▷Why are you interested in attending Columbia University?(200 words or fewer)</p>
<p>▷For applicants to Columbia College,please tell us what from your current and past experiences(either academic or personal)attracts you specifically to the areas of study that you previously noted in the application.(200 words or fewer)</p>
<p>▷For applicants to Columbia Engineering,please tell us what from your current and past experiences(either academic or personal)attracts you specifically to the areas of study that you previously noted in the application.(200 words or fewer)</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p7.itc.cn/images01/20200814/8618100c794446bc94ba6d6f87802461.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p>一共有四个清单和四个短问题回答也就是小文书、四篇文书中有两篇为所有人必写，后两篇是分别针对哥伦比亚学院和工程学院申请人的要求。</p>
<p>官网说明中写three short answer questions，我想要么是说每个学生实际要写的是三篇，要么是笔误没改，因为去年是总共三个题目，一篇是所有人都需完成的Why school，另两篇分别是哥伦比亚学院和工程院申请人需完成的Why major补充文书。今年在维持Why school和Why major不变的基础上，比去年增加了一篇必选题：</p>
<p>哥伦比亚大学的学生在改善他们的社区中发挥着积极的作用，无论是在他们的宿舍、课堂还是整个纽约市。他们的行为，无论大小，都会对他人的生活产生积极的影响。分享你对你的家庭、学校、朋友圈或其他社区所做的贡献。(200单词以内)</p>
<p>去年的补充文书字数限制是不超过300个单词，今年全部改为了200个单词。看起来是减轻一点负担，实际篇幅短的文书可能更难写，因为必须更加精炼和主题突出。唱戏的台子变小了，戏还得一样精彩，难度自然是更大了。</p>
<p>列清单部分，去年是5个清单，今年减少了一个“列出描述你理想的大学社区的单词”，其余四个关于学校课程要求必读书目、课余读物、日常接触的媒体、喜欢的娱乐活动这些内容的清单基本保持不变。</p>
<p>对照补充文书部分的变化可以看出，这是把关于社区的话题从列清单简述扩展到写一篇完整的小文书，应该是重视度更提高了吧。四个清单中第一个是要了解你的学术思维，第二个是了解非学术阅读时间你读哪些书籍来娱乐消遣。</p>
<p>第三个清单要求列出你经常阅读的刊物和网站的名称。你认为与世界打交道最负责任的方式是什么?你认为可靠或有价值的信息来源是什么？除了简单地展示你与世界的接触，这份清单还可以揭示你最关心的具体政治和文化领域。注意对于有争议的网站要慎重填写，除非你附加说明经常阅读的恰当理由。</p>
<p>第四个清单要求列出过去一年中你最喜欢的电影、音乐会、表演、展览、讲座和其他娱乐活动，可以找一个中心主题来表达你的激情。</p>
<p>清单部分注意事项：使用逗号或分号分隔，不需要编号或解释或斜体或下划线，没有最低字数要求。字母顺序、时间顺序或按兴趣顺序排序均可。建议按时间或兴趣顺序。虽然要凸显你的与众不同，但最重要的还是真实，避免夸大和刻意迎合。</p>
<h1><strong>宾夕法尼亚大学</strong></h1>
<p>Penn-specific Essays</p>
<p>How did you discover your intellectual and academic interests,and how will you explore them at the University of Pennsylvania?Please respond considering the specific undergraduate school you have selected.(300-450 words)</p>
<p>At Penn,learning and growth happen outside of the classroom,too.How will you explore the community at Penn?Consider how this community will help shape your perspective and identity,and how your identity and perspective will help shape this community.(150-200 words)</p>
<p>这两篇补充文书基本和去年一样，第一篇是Why Essay。这篇的关键是要对宾大做充分的调研，学校官网一定要好好研究。其他途径的调研及访校也都是有帮助的，今年的疫情之下实地访校也可以用云访校来替代。推荐阅读：Admissions Officer告诉你Why Essay写作攻略|http://www.lxws.net/new.php?id=801</p>
<p>云访校，调研过程中对所有吸引你的东西做详细的笔记。调研尽可能的深入些，可以了解一下意向专业的相关课程，还可以通过网络搜索一下授课的教授。</p>
<p>宾大的这篇Why Essay强调了学术，所以应聚焦于你对所申请专业的的学术兴趣和追求，以及UPenn将如何帮助你实现你的目标，目的就是向招生官表明，宾大是多么的适合你和你的学业目标。</p>
<p>第二篇是一个非常典型的“Why You?”文书，关注点是社区而不是学术。要回答这个问题，可以考虑看看宾大有哪些学生俱乐部和活动（官网链接：https://admissions.upenn.edu/living-at-penn/student-activities），找到一些符合你兴趣的。思考下你期望这些俱乐部和活动对你的未来有什么影响?</p>
<p>注意不要忘记问题还有后半部分！UPenn还想知道你将如何塑造社区，而不仅仅是它将如何塑造你。你会带来哪些独特的视角？你能做什么别人做不到的事?</p>
<p>对于双学位和特殊项目还有额外的文书要求，根据申请项目不同选择不同的文书题目：</p>
<p>For students applying to the coordinated dual-degree and specialized programs,please answer these questions in regard to your single-degree school choice;your interest in the coordinated dual-degree or specialized program may be addressed through the program-specific essay.</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p0.itc.cn/images01/20200814/8e99fbc89fdf457eb169a9bedf8e8dc9.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<h1><strong>达特茅斯学院</strong></h1>
<p>❶While arguing a Dartmouth-related case before the U.S.Supreme Court in 1818,Daniel Webster,Class of 1801,delivered this memorable line:"It is,sir,…a small college,and yet there are those who love it!"As you seek admission to the Class of 2025,what aspects of the College's program,community,or campus environment attract your interest?</p>
<p>❷ 六选一，250-300字</p>
<p>A) The Hawaiian word mo'olelo is often translated as"story"but it can also refer to history,legend,genealogy,and tradition.Use one of these translations to introduce yourself.</p>
<p>B) What excites you?</p>
<p>C) In The Boy Who Harnessed the Wind,William Kamkwamba,Class of 2014,reflects on constructing a windmill from recycled materials to power the electrical appliances in his family's Malawian house:"If you want to make it,all you have to do is try."What drives you to create and what do you hope to make or have you already made?</p>
<p>D) Curiosity is a guiding element of Toni Morrison's talent as a writer."I feel totally curious and alive and in control.And almost...magnificent,when I write,"she says.Celebrate your curiosity.</p>
<p>E) "Everything changes,everything moves,everything revolves,everything flies and goes away,"observed Frida Kahlo.Apply Kahlo's perspective to your own life.</p>
<p>F) In the aftermath of World War II,Dartmouth President John Sloane Dickey,Class of 1929,proclaimed,"The world's troubles are your troubles…and there is nothing wrong with the world that better human beings cannot fix."Which of the world's"troubles"inspires you to act?How might your course of study at Dartmouth prepare you to address it?</p>
<h1><strong>西北大学</strong></h1>
<p>In the Northwestern Writing Supplement,we ask students to explain why they would like to attend Northwestern.This question is intentionally open-ended.You may choose one or several aspects of Northwestern to focus your writing,though the majority of the essay’s content should relate to your own interests or experiences.</p>
<h1><strong>圣母大学</strong></h1>
<p>必写一，200字以内</p>
<p>The founder of the Congregation of Holy Cross,Blessed Basil Moreau,wrote,“We shall always place education side by side with instruction;the mind will not be cultivated at the expense of the heart.”How do you hope a Notre Dame education and experience will transform your mind and heart?</p>
<p>必写二，五选二，200字以内</p>
<p>❶A Notre Dame education is not just for you,but also for those who will benefit from the impact you make.Who do you aspire to serve after you graduate?</p>
<p>❷ In response to the rising momentum behind the Black Lives Matter movement during June 2020,G.Marcus Cole,the Joseph A.Matson Dean of the Notre Dame Law School,penned an open letter entitled,“I am George Floyd.Except I can breathe.And I can do something.”He issues a call to the Notre Dame community saying,“Each of us must do what we can,wherever we are.”What is one action you are taking“to change this world for the better?”</p>
<p>❸God and the Good Life is an interdisciplinary course created by the departments of Philosophy and Film,Television,and Theatre that asks students to consider moral questions about what they believe and how they want to live their lives.What do God and a good life mean to you?</p>
<p>❹Notre Dame has a rich history deeply rooted in tradition.Share how a favorite tradition from your life has impacted who you are today.</p>
<p>❺ What brings you joy?</p>
<h1><strong>埃默里大学</strong></h1>
<p>两篇小文书，要求是：从“Reflections”和“Tell us about you”这两组题目里各选一个题目回答，每篇不超过150字。</p>
<p>“Reflections”Category</p>
<p>Respond to one of the following.</p>
<p>▷Share about a time when you questioned something that you believed to be true.</p>
<p>▷If you could go back in time,what advice would you offer yourself at the beginning of secondary/high school?</p>
<p>▷Reflect on a personal experience where you intentionally expanded your cultural awareness.</p>
<p>这三个问题中只有第一题和去年相同，后两题均为今年新题。</p>
<p>“Tell us about you”Category</p>
<p>Respond to one of the following.</p>
<p>▷Which book,character,song,or piece of work(fiction or non-fiction)represents you,and why?</p>
<p>▷ If you could witness a historic event first-hand,what would it be,and why?</p>
<p>▷Introduce yourself to your first-year Emory University roommate.</p>
<p>这三个问题中第一和第二题和去年相同，最后一题为今年新题。</p>
<p>第一篇小文书需要写的是“反思”。从三个提示中选择一个提示来回答，这些提示会让你思考一些对你有意义的事情，那些帮助你成长至今的事情，可以是你的经历，你获得的见解，亦或是你热爱的领域。</p>
<p>第二篇小文书要从“告诉我们关于你的事”的三个提示中选择一个回答。这三个提示集中在你如何看待自己和你的措辞表达，这样招生官可以了解到在你的申请材料其他部分看不到的关于你的个性和兴趣的各个方面。</p>
<p>Extra/Supplemental essay是学校用来检验学生性格与学校整体氛围契合度的文书材料，平均每所大学要求申请人提供2-3篇补充文书，一轮申请季可能要写至少20篇文书，这个工作量让许多同学头大，所以一定要提前拟稿。</p>
➜2020秋季美国各大学学费政策盘点
http://www.sohu.com/a/413118620_490529	28466
<p>今年美国大学政策改了又改，截止目前，许多大学基本确定：<strong>新学期将会以网课形式授课！</strong></p>
<p>然而，网课虽然被同学们玩出了隔空借笔，集体掉线……等各种花样，但根据One Class对美国13,606名大学生的调查：</p>
<ul>
<li>3/4的学生对在线课程的质量表示不满意；</li>
<li><strong>超过93%的学生认为，上网课应该降学费！</strong></li>
</ul>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p0.itc.cn/images01/20200814/cf4d9404e23a4a4e93a61b296dd45fd7.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p><strong>高校官宣：学费，我降还不行吗！</strong></p>
<p>同学们降学费的要求合情合理，呼声又大，学校再躺着装睡似乎说不过去。</p>
<p>就有高校官宣了：<strong>这学费，我降了！</strong></p>
<p>🏫<strong>普林斯顿大学</strong>7月6日率先官宣：<strong>降低10%学费</strong>至48,500美元/年。</p>
<p>同时还承诺，不会收取任何活动或体育费用，将按比例分配食宿费用。</p>
<p>理由嘛，普林斯顿校长认为：远程学习不能提供沉浸式的学习环境（感动哭了，就喜欢这么讲道理的校长）。</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p8.itc.cn/images01/20200814/2d96e2461b81420da07c7ff1d8be2f33.png" max-width="600"><span class="img-desc" style="font-size: 16px;">图/官网</span></img></p>            <div class="lookall-box">
